60. Notes on vetting the found explanantia

    judging that none is acceptable
        : see @ ../60.vetting_their_explanantia.brec
        argument
            - none of the soley physics/nature-based explanations satisfies
                ∵ each leaves a residue of unexplained surprise at reality being so structured
                  that hardly could a viable, life-supporting cosmos exist unless (surprise!)
                  it also afforded a long-term safehold for mind
                    : re `leaves a residue of unexplained surprise`
                      see `^*b\) SPP reduction as a search criterion$` @ notes.brec
                    ∵ one then wonders at such open questions as: what constraint on reality
                      so slims the possibilities?  whence comes it, and why?
                    / thus the residue of surprise and the call for a more satisfying explanation
        feasiblity
            - prospects for refuting the claim: hardly could life exist absent a speed limit on causation
                : cf. `a necessarily tight coupling between.+habitability and safeholding capacity`p
                  @ `^*- the added premise.+for the multiverse.+hypothesis to explain.+the safehold`s
                  @ ../../text.notes.brec : the more general form of this threatening claim
                ⇒ promising
                    - claimants’ arguments expose premises that feel weak on probing
                    - they invite attack
                ⇒ good, undercutting the claim by invoking the open-endedness of the multiverse ensemble
                    : see notepad:2026-5-28e : inherent counter-fundamentalism of the multiverse ensemble
                      hypothesis owing to its effective infinite open-endedness|unboundedness
                      in regard to the structure of reality
                    - analysis, in light of the presence of the safehold,
                      of the explanantial|explanatory space|field of {the fine-tuning field|fine-tuning},
                      namely of these hypotheses together:
                            • necessity
                                - either it is greatly weakened
                                    ∵ now it has much more to explain
                                - or left like multiverse ensemble
                                    / viz. untouched but useless for explaining the safehold
                            • multiverse ensemble
                                - it is left untouched
                                - but it leaves the safehold unexplained
                                    : see `^*: see notepad:.+counter-fundamentalism of.+multiverse` :
                                      owing to which it cannot claim a fundamentally necessary
                                      (nor even probable) linkage between support for basic life
                                      and the presence of the safehold
                            • design
                                - it can explain the safehold
                                - but it leaves unexplained the presence of a designer
                    - based on this analysis, I [have cause to] try joining one of the former hypotheses
                      with the latter (designer) to form a single, combined explanation
                        - an obvious combination method: one hypothesis as explanans,
                          the other as explanandum
                            - then I have two choices re the role of design/designer
                                - only one choice improves on the status quo
                                    - viz. design/designer as explanandum
                                - but the improvement is better with multiverse ensemble as the explanans
                                    ∵ (again) necessity is greatly weakened in this role
                    - now the effective infinite open-endedness|unboundedness of the multiverse ensemble
                      makes the (eventual) presence of a successful designer plausible, if not inevitable
                        : re `effective infinite open-endedness|unboundedness`
                          see `^*: see notepad:2026-5-28e.+${same}`s
                    ? must it indeed be so open-ended|unbounded?
                        ⇒ yes, at least presently
                            - cursory reading indicates the ensemble (if it exists) is likely to be:
                                • huge, perhaps 500 orders of magnitude, if not unbounded
                                • diverse in the extreme, incalculably at present
                                    ∵ insight is restricted at present to highly parametized models,
                                      unable to penetrate to any underlying layer of law that might
                                      govern the variation of their parameters
                                : e.g. https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/fine-tuning/#FineTuniMult :
                                 ‘Fine-tuning and the multiverse’ (§ 4)
                                    : see @ `^*• multiverse ensemble$` @
                                      40.a_search_for_explanations.notes.brec
                                / esp. Ćirković. ‘Stranger things: multiverse, string cosmology,
                                  physical eschatology’ (chapter 12)
                                    : see @ `^*• multiverse ensemble$` @
                                      40.a_search_for_explanations.notes.brec
                            ∴ any linkage of life’s basic enablements (whose fine-tuning is explained
                              by the multiverse hypothesis) to the existence of the safehold
                              is likely to be weak
                                - most instances in the huge and diverse set of model parametizations
                                  will realize a basic enablement of life without also realizing
                                  a viable safehold, let alone a near-ideal one like we witness
                                    : N.B. notepad:2026-5-31d : the importance here of considering
                                      the full property set of the safehold, including e.g.
                                      the electroweak vacuum meta-stability that allows it
                                      to persist for much longer (by orders of magnitude)
                                      than the mere generation of intelligent life takes
                ⇒ better to neutralize the threat and win the issue over to my favour
                  by giving an alternative (or being agnostic, additional) explanans,
                  one that is more convincing than necessity
                    : see @ ../../text.notes.brec
